            <tr><td><strong>Kenta Adachi</strong></td><td>Japan</td><td>80:41</td><td>2022</td><td>Current Guinness World Record</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Harald Riise</td><td>Norway</td><td>16:03</td><td>2021</td><td>Previous record holder</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Tazio Gavioli</td><td>Italy</td><td>13:52</td><td>2018</td><td>Former record holder</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p>The men's record progressed steadily and then jumped dramatically. Tazio Gavioli held 13 minutes 52 seconds in 2018, Harald Riise extended it to 16 minutes 3 seconds in 2021, and Kenta Adachi then set a new mark of 80 minutes 41 seconds in 2022, more than four times the previous record.</p>

        <h2 id="female-records">Women's Dead Hang Records</h2>
        <p>Guinness World Records lists the longest duration in the dead hang position above as an open category. It also recognises age group female records, such as the oldest woman to hold a dead hang position. Guinness does not publish a single widely cited open female duration record to match the men's mark.</p>
        <p>In practice, elite female climbers and grip athletes hold long dead hangs. Lower average bodyweight gives women a favorable strength to weight ratio for hanging, and trained female climbers routinely hold dead hangs beyond 3 minutes.</p>

        <h2 id="record-history">Dead Hang Record History &amp; Timeline</h2>
